cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it as below. If you use one of
  the specific third-party models/algorithms it wraps (QuPepFold,
  QFold, ZairaChem, Boltz-2, RFdiffusion, etc.), please ALSO cite that
  work directly using the entries under `references` below, or the
  citation given in that model's own repository.
title: "qFoldIT Protein-Design-MCP"
version: "0.2.0"
date-released: 2026-07-11
url: "https://github.com/qfoldit/Protein-Design-MCP"
repository-code: "https://github.com/qfoldit/Protein-Design-MCP"
license: Apache-2.0
type: software
authors:
  - name: "qFoldIT"
    # Individual contributor/consortium-member names are added here
    # only with their explicit, on-record consent (see CONTRIBUTING.md
    # and claude-skills/CONTRIBUTING.md for this repo's existing
    # policy). This file does not list named individuals who have not
    # confirmed they wish to be credited in this exact role, so no
    # personal names are included here -- add them once confirmed.
references:
  - type: article
    title: >-
      QuPepFold: A python package for hybrid quantum-classical protein
      folding simulations with CVaR-optimized VQE
    authors:
      - name: "Akshay Uttarkar"
      - name: "Vidya Niranjan"
      - name: "Amit Saxena"
      - name: "Vinay Kumar"
    journal: "PLOS ONE"
    year: 2026
    month: 2
    identifiers:
      - type: doi
        value: "10.1371/journal.pone.0342012"
    notes: >-
      CVaR-VQE peptide folding basis for
      src/protein_design_mcp/pipelines/quantum_runner.py's
      predict_peptide_quantum_vqe / QuPepFoldRunner. NOTE: this
      wrapper's exact call signature into the qupepfold package was
      written from this paper's abstract-level description only and
      was not independently verified against the installed package's
      Python API -- see the module docstring before relying on it.
  - type: article
    title: "QFold: quantum walks and deep learning to solve protein folding"
    authors:
      - name: "P. A. M. Casares"
      - name: "Roberto Campos"
      - name: "M. A. Martin-Delgado"
    journal: "Quantum Science and Technology"
    volume: 7
    issue: 2
    pages: "025013"
    year: 2022
    identifiers:
      - type: doi
        value: "10.1088/2058-9565/ac4f2f"
      - type: other
        value: "arXiv:2101.10279"
    notes: >-
      Original continuous off-lattice, torsion-angle quantum-walk
      Metropolis methodology that
      src/protein_design_mcp/pipelines/quantum_runner.py's
      simulate_quantum_walk_fold takes classical inspiration from. That
      function is an explicitly-documented CLASSICAL approximation of
      this paper's quantum-walk metaphor (a biased random walk driving
      a real Metropolis acceptance step, not a quantum circuit
      simulation) -- see that module's docstring for the full scope
      note. It does not reproduce this paper's IBMQ Casablanca
      hardware results.
  - type: article
    title: >-
      Hybrid organic-inorganic structures trigger the formation of
      primitive cell-like compartments
    authors:
      - name: "Silvia Holler"
      - name: "Stuart Bartlett"
      - name: "Richard J. G. Löffler"
      - name: "Federica Casiraghi"
      - name: "Claro Ignacio Sainz Diaz"
      - name: "Julyan H. E. Cartwright"
      - name: "Martin M. Hanczyc"
    journal: "Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences"
    volume: 120
    issue: 33
    pages: "e2300491120"
    year: 2023
    identifiers:
      - type: doi
        value: "10.1073/pnas.2300491120"
    notes: >-
      Included per this repository's stated multi-paradigm scope
      (spatial/protocell digital-twin context for OpenUSD/NanoVer
      export). Not currently wrapped by any specific tool in this
      codebase -- listed for attribution/context only, at the
      requester's direction.
  - type: article
    title: >-
      First fully-automated AI/ML virtual screening cascade implemented
      at a drug discovery centre in Africa
    authors:
      - name: "Gemma Turon"
      - name: "Jason Hlozek"
      - name: "John G. Woodland"
      - name: "Ankur Kumar"
      - name: "Kelly Chibale"
      - name: "Miquel Duran-Frigola"
    journal: "Nature Communications"
    volume: 14
    pages: "5736"
    year: 2023
    identifiers:
      - type: doi
        value: "10.1038/s41467-023-41512-2"
    notes: >-
      ZairaChem AutoML QSAR tool, co-developed with and validated at
      the H3D Centre (University of Cape Town). Wrapped by
      pipelines/zairachem_runner.py, tools/predict_bioactivity.py,
      tools/train_qsar_model.py, and tools/predict_admet_profile.py.
      Pretrained malaria/tuberculosis screening-cascade models:
      https://github.com/ersilia-os/h3d-screening-cascade-models
  - type: software
    title: "Boltz-2"
    notes: >-
      Structure/affinity prediction wrapped by
      pipelines/boltz_runner.py, tools/boltz_predict.py -- see that
      project's own repository (https://github.com/jwohlwend/boltz)
      for its canonical citation, which was not re-verified here.
  - type: software
    title: "RFdiffusion"
    notes: >-
      Backbone generation wrapped by pipelines/rfdiffusion.py -- see
      that project's own repository
      (https://github.com/RosettaCommons/RFdiffusion) for its
      canonical citation, which was not re-verified here.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  - type: software
    title: "Virtual-Lab-Simulation"
    authors:
      - name: "Neil Voss"
    url: "https://github.com/qfoldit/Virtual-Lab-Simulation"
    repository-code: "https://github.com/qfoldit/Virtual-Lab-Simulation"
    license: "LGPL-3.0"
    notes: >-
      Browser-based virtual-lab protocol simulation engine (YAML
      protocol authoring compiled to interactive TypeScript/SVG
      simulations). Confirmed via direct repository fetch on
      2026-07-11 -- "Maintained by Neil Voss". Non-code content is
      separately CC-BY-4.0 licensed (see the repository's own
      LICENSE.CC_BY_4_0). Not currently wrapped or vendored by any tool
      in this codebase; listed for attribution/context at the
      requester's direction. No associated journal article or DOI was
      found for this work -- it is cited here as software, not as a
      paper.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
